Creating Pills — Step by Step

1. Decide the elements. These are the values the user picks from — typically a static space-separated list like `"red green blue"`.

2. Choose selection mode: `"multi"` (toggle, space-separated list result) or `"single"` (one active value).

3. If you need to read the selection from another tiddler or widget, set `sync-tiddler` and `sync-field`. Otherwise the selection is only available internally.

4. Set an explicit `state` if you need stable state across re-renders (e.g., `$:/state/myapp/color-pills`). Omit for throwaway usage.

Minimal example (multi-select):

```
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/pills"
  elements="alpha beta gamma delta"
  selection="multi"
  state="$:/state/demo/pills"/>
```

Single-select with custom view:

```
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/pills"
  elements="red green blue"
  selection="single"
  sync-tiddler="$:/temp/chosen-color"
  sync-field="text">
  <$fill $name="view">
    <span style="color:<<element>>;">&#9679;</span> <<element>>
  </$fill>
</$transclude>
```

With filtering and on-select callback:

```
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/pills"
  elements="p-1 p-2 p-3 p-4 p-5 p-6 p-7 p-8"
  filterable="yes"
  selection="multi"
  state="$:/state/demo/filtered">
  <$fill $name="view">
    ''<$text text={{{[<element>uppercase[]]}}}/>''
  </$fill>
  <$fill $name="on-select">
    <$action-log message=`Selected: $(element)$`/>
  </$fill>
</$transclude>
```

Inline filter (search input above pills):

```
<$transclude $tiddler="$:/plugins/rimir/components/pills"
  elements="apple banana cherry date elderberry fig grape"
  filterable="inline"
  selection="multi"
  state="$:/state/demo/inline-filter"/>
```

Common patterns:

- **Tag picker**: `elements` = list of available tags, `sync-tiddler` = target tiddler, `sync-field` = `"tags"`
- **Filter toggle**: `elements` = filter options, read selection from `sync-tiddler` and use it in a filter elsewhere
- **Dynamic elements**: Use a filter run as `elements` value, e.g., `elements="[tag[Color]get[title]]"` — but note pills treats this as a space-separated literal list, NOT a filter. For dynamic lists, pre-compute and pass as a variable.
